In Google Charts, when using the Apps Script API, you can set the tick mark size in a **line chart** by customizing the **hAxis.ticks** and **vAxis.ticks** options.

To control the **tick mark size**, you generally adjust the **font size** for the axis labels using `hAxis.textStyle` and `vAxis.textStyle`. However, if you're specifically referring to the **tick length**, Google Charts does not provide a direct way to set the tick mark size, but you can control the appearance of ticks using `hAxis.ticks` and `gridlines`.

### Example: Adjusting Tick Appearance in Google Apps Script
```javascript
function drawChart() {
  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getActiveSheet();
  var data = Charts.newDataTable()
    .addColumn(Charts.ColumnType.STRING, "X-Axis")
    .addColumn(Charts.ColumnType.NUMBER, "Value")
    .addRow(["A", 10])
    .addRow(["B", 20])
    .addRow(["C", 30])
    .addRow(["D", 40])
    .build();

  var chart = Charts.newLineChart()
    .setDataTable(data)
    .setOptions({
      title: "Sample Line Chart",
      hAxis: {
        title: "Categories",
        textStyle: { fontSize: 14 },  // Adjust axis label size
        ticks: [{v: 0, f: "A"}, {v: 1, f: "B"}, {v: 2, f: "C"}, {v: 3, f: "D"}]  // Control tick positions
      },
      vAxis: {
        title: "Values",
        textStyle: { fontSize: 14 },  // Adjust vertical axis label size
        gridlines: { count: 5 }  // Controls the number of horizontal grid lines
      },
      height: 400,
      width: 600,
      curveType: "function"
    })
    .build();

  sheet.insertChart(chart);
}
```

### Explanation:
- `hAxis.textStyle.fontSize`: Controls the tick label size.
- `hAxis.ticks`: Defines the tick positions and labels.
- `vAxis.gridlines.count`: Adjusts how many gridlines appear, indirectly affecting tick marks.

